2. The waterproof structure of claim 1, further comprising:
a first receiving partition wall and a second receiving partition wall formed in each of the first housing and the second housings, respectively;
a first receiving recess and a second receiving recess surrounded by each of the first receiving partition wall and the second receiving partition wall, respectively; and
a first through-hole and a second through-hole extending from the first receiving recess and the second receiving recess and communicating with the outside of each the first housing and the second housings, respectively, through the first receiving partition wall and the second receiving partition wall, respectively;
wherein the first wiring hole and the second wiring hole extends from the first receiving recess and second receiving recess to the inside of each of the first housing and second housing, respectively, through the first receiving partition wall and the second receiving partition wall facing the first through hole and second through-hole, respectively, and is disposed on a substantially straight line with respect to the first through-hole and the second through-hole, respectively.
